  <h1 class="article-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <div class="article-meta">Last updated <span id="masthead-date-2">—</span></div>

  <div class="article-body">
    <p>This policy explains what information RumorMouth collects, how it's used, and the choices you have. We've written it to reflect how the site actually works today, plus how it will work once features noted below (like advertising) go live.</p>

    <p><strong>Who we are.</strong> RumorMouth (rumormouth.com) is an independently run entertainment site. For any privacy question, contact <a href="mailto:hello@rumormouth.com">hello@rumormouth.com</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Hosting and basic logs.</strong> This site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Like virtually every website, Cloudflare's network automatically processes standard technical data to deliver pages — things like IP address, browser type, and request timestamps. This happens at the infrastructure level to serve you the site; RumorMouth itself does not separately collect or store this data. Cloudflare's own privacy practices are described at <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Cookies and advertising.</strong> RumorMouth does not currently run advertising. If and when we do (for example, through Google AdSense), that section will use cookies and similar technologies to serve and measure ads, and this policy will be updated accordingly before those ads go live. Where required, we'll provide a consent mechanism for visitors in regions like the EU/UK.</p>

    <p><strong>Affiliate links.</strong> Some original articles may contain affiliate links — meaning RumorMouth may earn a small commission if you make a purchase through them, at no extra cost to you. We'll disclose this directly on any post that includes one.</p>

    <p><strong>Outside links.</strong> The Wire links out to the original outlets we curate from (Variety, TMZ, and others); the Release section republishes content from licensed wire services like PR Newswire. Once you click through, that site's own privacy policy applies, not this one.</p>

    <p><strong>What we don't do.</strong> We don't currently require account creation, and we don't sell personal information to third parties.</p>

    <p><strong>Your rights.</strong> Depending on where you're located, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal data we hold about you, or to object to certain processing — for example under the EU/UK GDPR or the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA). To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:hello@rumormouth.com">hello@rumormouth.com</a>.</p>

    <p><strong>Children's privacy.</strong> RumorMouth is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from them.</p>

    <p><strong>Changes to this policy.</strong> We'll update this page when our practices change — most notably once advertising or other data-collecting features launch — and update the date above when we do.</p>

    <p style="font-size: 14px; opacity: 0.65; margin-top: 40px;">This policy is provided for general transparency and isn't a substitute for legal advice. If you have specific compliance requirements, consult a lawyer familiar with your jurisdiction.</p>
  </div>

